observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management instruct the LSB to undertake the following:
Strictly comply with the prescribed timelines for the preparation and submission of SEF utilization reports to all concerned offices;
Enhance awareness of the LSB on compliance with the reporting requirements under DepEd-DBM-DILG JC No. 1, series of 2017;
Post the SEF utilization reports in the municipality’s website in order maximize the websites potential and to increase transparency; and
Establish internal procedures and enhance internal control to properly monitor documents/information pertaining to SEF and to strengthen financial accountability and transparency in the utilization of the said fund.

We recommended that Management require the responsible officers to:

conduct physical count of all local roads under the Municipality’s jurisdiction and submit the prescribed RPCRN System;

review further the list of non-existing/missing Road Networks submitted with a total cost of P72,126,749.84 if these were replaced, washed out by flood, etc. and derecognized in the books;

prepare the Report on LRNs, maintain local road inventory, road map and property cards for all roads and its components;

maintain subsidiary ledger cards for roads and road components of every road network and prepare lapsing schedule showing the computation of the depreciation of each component of the Road Network System;

Disclose the total Road Network System in the Notes to Financial Statement (NFS) and make adjusting entry regarding derecognition of replaced assets, if any, following the provision of COA Circular 2015-008; and provide a complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

